The population of bats in Scotland and the UK has declined significantly over the last century.
They are threatened by works on construction and development, which negatively affect the litter and loss of habitat.
Windmills and lighting can also pose a risk, including sticky paper and chemical processing of building materials, and domestic cat attacks.
The bats aren't actually blind.
