They use sophisticated echo-location technique to locate bugs and obstacles on their flight path.
NTS, which cares for more than 270 historic buildings, 38 important gardens and 76,000 hectares of land across the country, takes the bats very seriously.
There are ten trained experts who regularly carry out checks, inspection of litter, and sometimes rescue.
