He emphasizes how important it is to check if the bats are on the property, as it is possible that the accidental destruction of one mother's litter will kill up to 400 females and young people, which is likely to result in the extermination of the entire local population.
The bats are protected animals and the law prohibits them from killing, harassing, harassing or destroying their nests.
Elisabeth Ferrell, an officer of the Scottish Bat Conservation Fund, encouraged the public to get involved and help.
